Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), dh-python, dh-sequence-python3, dh-sequence-sphinxdoc, pybuild-plugin-pyproject, python3-all, python3-hatchling, python3-plumbum, python3-setuptools, python3-sphinx <!nodoc>, python3-sphinx-rtd-theme <!nodoc>
Description: Python 3 library for remote procedure calls RPyC (pronounced as are-pie-see), or Remote Python Call, is a transparent Python library for symmetrical remote procedure calls, clustering and distributed-computing. RPyC makes use of object-proxying, a technique that employs Python’s dynamic nature, to overcome the physical boundaries between processes and computers, so that remote objects can be manipulated as if they were local.
Package-List: python3-rpyc deb python optional arch=all python3-rpyc-doc deb doc optional arch=all
